status: MARC21-007: Groove width/groove pitch of sound recording
Width of the groove of the recording for discs or the pitch of the groove for cylinders.

definition (en): Microgroove disc or a fine cylinder.
scope note (en): Discs issued at 16, 33 1/3, and 45 rpm are usually issued as microgroove. Cylinders issued at 160 rpm (which have 200 grooves per inch) are usually issued as fine.
Used for tapes and compact audio discs.
Discs issued at 78 rpm are usually coarse. Cylinders issued at 120 rpm (which have 100 grooves per inch) are usually standard.

definition (en): Groove width/groove pitch is not known.
Groove width/groove pitch other than microgroove/fine, coarse/standard.
